#. <section class="sutta" id="sn7.21"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn7.21:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 7"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 7"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn7.21:0.2"
msgid "2. Upāsakavagga"
msgstr "2. Lay Followers"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn7.21:0.3"
msgid "21. Saṅgāravasutta"
msgstr "21. With Saṅgārava"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.183"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.394"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.21:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn7.21:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena saṅgāravo nāma brāhmaṇo sāvatthiyaṃ paṭivasati "
"udakasuddhiko, udakena parisuddhiṃ pacceti, sāyaṃ pātaṃ "
"udakorohanānuyogamanuyutto viharati."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time there was a brahmin named Saṅgārava staying in Sāvatthī. He "
"practiced purification by water, believing in purification by water. He "
"lived committed to the practice of immersing himself in water at dawn and "
"dusk."

msgctxt "sn7.21:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ "
"piṇḍāya pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Ānanda robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, "
"entered Sāvatthī for alms."

msgctxt "sn7.21:1.4"
msgid ""
"Sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yena bhagavā "
"tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. "
"Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"He wandered for alms in Sāvatthī. After the meal, on his return from alms-"
"round, he went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:"

msgctxt "sn7.21:1.5"
msgid ""
"“idha, bhante, saṅgāravo nāma brāhmaṇo sāvatthiyaṃ paṭivasati udakasuddhiko, "
"udakena suddhiṃ pacceti, sāyaṃ pātaṃ udakorohanānuyogamanuyutto viharati."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, there is a brahmin named Saṅgārava staying in Sāvatthī. He practices "
"purification by water, believing in purification by water. He lives "
"committed to the practice of immersing himself in water at dawn and dusk."

msgctxt "sn7.21:1.6"
msgid ""
"Sādhu, bhante, bhagavā yena saṅgāravassa brāhmaṇassa nivesanaṃ "
"tenupasaṅkamatu anukampaṃ upādāyā”ti."
msgstr "Please visit him at his home out of compassion.”"

msgctxt "sn7.21:1.7"
msgid "Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena."
msgstr "The Buddha consented in silence."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.21:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena "
"saṅgāravassa brāhmaṇassa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte "
"āsane nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, went "
"to the home of the brahmin Saṅgārava, and sat down on the seat spread out."

msgctxt "sn7.21:2.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho saṅgāravo brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr ""
"Then the brahmin Saṅgārava went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings "
"with him."

msgctxt "sn7.21:2.3"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinnaṃ kho saṅgāravaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side. The Buddha said to him:"

msgctxt "sn7.21:2.4"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, brāhmaṇa, udakasuddhiko, udakena suddhiṃ paccesi, sāyaṃ "
"pātaṃ udakorohanānuyogamanuyutto viharasī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Is it really true, brahmin, that you practice purification by water, "
"believing in purification by water; that you live committed to the practice "
"of immersing yourself in water at dawn and dusk?”"

msgctxt "sn7.21:2.5"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bho gotama”."
msgstr "“Yes, Master Gotama.”"

msgctxt "sn7.21:2.6"
msgid ""
"“Kiṃ pana tvaṃ, brāhmaṇa, atthavasaṃ sampassamāno udakasuddhiko, "
"udakasuddhiṃ paccesi, sāyaṃ pātaṃ udakorohanānuyogamanuyutto viharasī”ti?"
msgstr "“But brahmin, for what reason do you practice purification by water?”"

# This is a very precise and clear statement of the pre-Buddhist quasi-physical understanding of good and evil. Such practices, which are detailed further in the Jatakas, clearly relate to magical thinking. Evidently such quasi-material thinking was shared between the Brahmins (at least some of them) and the Jains.
#. VAR: Idha me, bho gotama → idha me bho gotama ahaṃ (pts1, mr)
#. VAR: nhānena → nahānena (bj, pts1) | sayaṃ nhānena (s3, km)
msgctxt "sn7.21:2.7"
msgid ""
"“Idha me, bho gotama, yaṃ divā pāpakammaṃ kataṃ hoti, taṃ sāyaṃ nhānena "
"pavāhemi, yaṃ rattiṃ pāpakammaṃ kataṃ hoti taṃ pātaṃ nhānena pavāhemi."
msgstr ""
"“It’s because, Master Gotama, whatever bad deeds I’ve done during the day I "
"wash off by bathing at dusk; and whatever bad deeds I’ve done during the "
"night, I wash off by bathing at dawn."

msgctxt "sn7.21:2.8"
msgid ""
"Imaṃ khvāhaṃ, bho gotama, atthavasaṃ sampassamāno udakasuddhiko, udakena "
"suddhiṃ paccemi, sāyaṃ pātaṃ udakorohanānuyogamanuyutto viharāmī”ti."
msgstr "That’s the reason why I practice purification by water.”"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.395"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.21:3.1"
msgid "“Dhammo rahado brāhmaṇa sīlatittho,"
msgstr "“The teaching is a lake with shores of ethics, brahmin,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.21:3.2"
msgid "Anāvilo sabbhi sataṃ pasattho;"
msgstr "unclouded, praised by the fine to the good."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.21:3.3"
msgid "Yattha have vedaguno sinātā,"
msgstr "There the knowledge-masters go to bathe,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Anallagattāva → anallīnagattāva (mr)
msgctxt "sn7.21:3.4"
msgid "Anallagattāva taranti pāran”ti."
msgstr "and cross to the far shore without getting wet.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.21:4.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, saṅgāravo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he had spoken, Saṅgārava said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn7.21:4.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe …"
msgstr "“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent! …"

msgctxt "sn7.21:4.3"
msgid ""
"upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti."
msgstr ""
"From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has "
"gone for refuge for life.”"
